#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:3
msgid "/proc/sys/debug/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:5
msgid ""
"These files show up in ``/proc/sys/debug/``, depending on the kernel "
"configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:11
msgid "exception-trace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:13
msgid ""
"This flag controls whether the kernel prints information about unhandled "
"signals (like segmentation faults) to the kernel log (``dmesg``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:16
msgid "``0``: Unhandled signals are not traced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:17
msgid "``1``: Information about unhandled signals is printed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:19
msgid ""
"The default value is ``1`` on most architectures (like x86, MIPS, RISC-V), "
"but it is ``0`` on **arm64**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:22
msgid ""
"The actual information printed and the context provided varies significantly "
"depending on the CPU architecture. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:25
msgid ""
"On **x86**, it typically prints the instruction pointer (IP), error code, "
"and address that caused a page fault."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:27
msgid ""
"On **PowerPC**, it may print the next instruction pointer (NIP), link "
"register (LR), and other relevant registers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:30
msgid ""
"When enabled, this feature is often rate-limited to prevent the kernel log "
"from being flooded during a crash loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:34
msgid "kprobes-optimization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:36
msgid ""
"This flag enables or disables the optimization of Kprobes on certain "
"architectures (like x86)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:39
msgid "``0``: Kprobes optimization is turned off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:40
msgid "``1``: Kprobes optimization is turned on (default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/sysctl/debug.rst:42
msgid ""
"For more details on Kprobes and its optimization, please refer to "
"Documentation/trace/kprobes.rst."
msgstr ""

